I"C<h2 id="hosting-a-static-website-on-amazon-s3">Hosting a Static Website on Amazon S3</h2>

<p>First of all, what is a static website? A static website includes any static content such as HTML pages and CSS files. They may also include client-side scripts made in JavaScript, which is only run within the clientâ€™s browser.</p>

<p>Now in comparision, what is a dynamic website? A dynamic website contains static content, and it along with dynamically generated content as well. This dynamic content is generated from server-side scripting languages such as PHP and ASP. When a website is dynamic, it allows for more customization and functionality than a static website.</p>

<h2 id="what-is-amazon-s3">What is Amazon S3?</h2>

<p>Amazon S3 is a cloud-based storage solution offered by AWS. You have the ability to store files or objects in the cloud, which allows high availability and low latency access to your files. It can also be used for storing data for backups and disaster recovery.</p>

<h2 id="setting-up-website-hosting-on-amazon-s3">Setting Up Website Hosting on Amazon S3</h2>

<h3 id="bucket-creation">Bucket creation</h3>
<ol>
  <li>First login to your AWS account and go to the AWS Management Console.</li>
  <li>Click Services on the top left, and search for â€œS3â€ and click on S3.</li>
  <li>Next, we want to create a bucket to store all of our files for our static website. Click â€œCreate bucketâ€.</li>
  <li>Enter the name of the bucket that you want to create.</li>
  <li>Select the region or location where you want to create your bucket.</li>
  <li>Click â€œNextâ€.</li>
  <li>Uncheck â€œBlock all public accessâ€. This needs to be unchecked because we want anybody to be able to visit our website.</li>
  <li>Check â€œI acknowledge that the current settings may result in this bucket and the objects within becoming publicâ€.</li>
  <li>Click â€œNextâ€.</li>
  <li>Review and verify your configuration for your bucket, before you create your bucket.</li>
  <li>Click â€œCreate bucketâ€.</li>
</ol>

<h3 id="configuring-static-website-hosting">Configuring static website hosting</h3>
<ol>
  <li>Next, click on the bucket that you just created. Click â€œPropertiesâ€.</li>
  <li>Click â€œStatic website hostingâ€.</li>
  <li>Click â€œUse this bucket to host a websiteâ€.</li>
  <li>Enter the name of your index document, usually itâ€™s â€œindex.htmlâ€.</li>
  <li>Click â€œSaveâ€.</li>
  <li>Now we want to upload the files that we want to host on our website. Click â€œUploadâ€.</li>
  <li>Select the files that you want to upload.</li>
  <li>Keep clicking â€œNextâ€ until you see the â€œUploadâ€ button. Click â€œUploadâ€.</li>
  <li>Next, we need to add a policy to our bucket to allow public access to the files in our bucket.</li>
  <li>Click on your bucket.</li>
  <li>Click â€œPermissionsâ€.</li>
  <li>Click â€œBucket Policyâ€.</li>
  <li>Copy this bucket policy and paste it into Bucket policy editor.
<code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">{
"Version": "2012-10-17",
"Statement": [
    {
        "Sid": "PublicReadGetObject",
        "Effect": "Allow",
        "Principal": "*",
        "Action": [
            "s3:GetObject"
        ],
        "Resource": [
            "arn:aws:s3:::example.com/*"
        ]
    }
]
}</code>
Replace â€œexample.comâ€ with the name of your bucket.</li>
  <li>Click â€œSaveâ€.</li>
  <li>Letâ€™s see if your website is up and running! Click â€œPropertiesâ€ and then â€œStatic website hostingâ€. Click on the Endpoint link.</li>
  <li>Now you should be able to see the files you uploaded and the website that you hosted on Amazon S3!</li>
</ol>

